adjectives.description: coincident (comparative more coincident, superlative most coincident)

entries.meaning: (of two events) Occurring at the same time.
examples: Of Riuallus, Gurgustius, Sysillius, Iago, and Kinimacus, rulers of Britaine by succession, and of the accidents coincident with their times.

entries.meaning: (of two objects) Being in the same location.
examples: Hitherto, the Universe of stars has always been considered as coincident with the Universe proper  […]
the whole Doctrine of Christianity teaches nothing, but what is perfectly suteable to, and coincident with, the Ruling Principles that a vertuous, and well Inclined man is Acted by;

entries.meaning: Either of multiple simultaneous related incidents
examples: When I was in London I was shocked at the alteration in our friend Tobin's looks and appearance. Those who always interpret two coincidents into cause and effect would surmise that marriage has been less conducive to his health than to his moral comfort.
